een returned</li>\n<li>Fixed course navigation not showing on open courses</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>4.0.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Added new getting started wizard</li>\n<li>Added learning paths (challenge exams)</li>\n<li>Added Stripe Connect integration</li>\n<li>Added course infobar Gutenberg block </li>\n<li>Added post status selectors to columns for post listing</li>\n<li>Added pagination for quizzes for ld_profile block and shortcode</li>\n<li>Added ability to use payment button shortcode for groups</li>\n<li>Added sample label in course builder for sample lessons</li>\n<li>Updated compatibility for widget preview for blocks with full site editing in WP 5.9 (FSE)</li>\n<li>Updated select2 library logic</li>\n<li>Updated REST API V2 Route v2/user/courses/ to include all course fields and certificates</li>\n<li>Fixed emails not sending as plain text</li>\n<li>Fixed error when switching to legacy theme</li>\n<li>Fixed new user email HTML content being received as an attachment</li>\n<li>Fixed purchasing access to a group sends the course purchase successs email</li>\n<li>Fixed conflict with all in one SEO (AISEO)</li>\n<li>Fixed PHP notices</li>\n<li>Fixed placeholder text on Select2 instances</li>\n</ul>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:82:\"LearnDash LMS Plugin - Turn your WordPress site into a learning management system.\";s:7:\"banners\";a:2:{s:3:\"low\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"high\";s:82:\"https://plugins.learndash.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/learndash-core_banner.jpg\";}s:11:\"screenshots\";a:1:{i:0;s:82:\"https://plugins.learndash.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/learndash-core_banner.jpg\";}s:5:\"icons\";a:1:{s:7:\"default\";s:76:\"https://plugins.learndash.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/ld-plugin-image.jpg\";}s:6:\"author\";s:9:\"LearnDash\";s:10:\"author_uri\";s:26:\"https://www.learndash.com/\";s:11:\"requires_ld\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"plugin_uri\";s:24:\"http://www.learndash.com\";s:4:\"tags\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"slug\";s:8:\"sfwd-lms\";s:12:\"product_type\";s:4:\"paid\";}s:15:\"learndash-notes\";a:20:{s:4:\"name\";s:5:\"Notes\";s:10:\"project_id\";i:172;s:14:\"latest_version\";s:5:\"1.1.1\";s:8:\"requires\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"tested\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"requires_php\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"last_updated\";s:19:\"2024-11-06 12:21:33\";s:8:\"sections\";a:3:{s:11:\"description\";s:114:\"The Notes add-on makes note-taking simple and opens up instructor communication during the student’s study time.\";s:12:\"installation\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:2231:\"<strong>1.1.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix - Resolved an issue where AJAX actions on frontend were not working properly.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.1.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Feature - Shortcode auto-injection now can be done per course content type.</li>\n<li>Feature - New Labels &quot;Change the help text next to &quot;Notify Instructor&quot; located below the new note editor&quot; and &quot;Change the additional help text that displays next to &quot;Notify Instructor&quot; located below the new note editor if &quot;Show All Student Notes to Instructors&quot; is enabled&quot; added to control text below the &quot;Notify Instructor&quot; setting when creating a Note.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Updated minimum required LearnDash LMS version to v4.7.0.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Rename the &quot;Features&quot; tab to &quot;Settings&quot; on the Settings page.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Rearrange tabs on the Settings Page to place &quot;Settings&quot; first.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Improved the &quot;How To&quot; tab on the Settings page.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Added actions: <code>learndash_notes_uninstall</code></li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.0.3</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix: Prevent fatal error when LearnDash LMS is deactivated while Notes by LearnDash is still active.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.0.2</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix: Removes code from downloaded Notes</li>\n<li>Fix: The minimize button now shows for the <code>[llms_add_new_note_popup]</code> shortcode with the TwentyTwenty Theme active</li>\n<li>Fix: Undefined array key when creating a Course</li>\n<li>Fix: Undefined array key when injecting a Menu Item into the Navigation Block</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.0.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix: Settings from other Notes Settings Tabs no longer get cleared out when a Notes Settings Tab get saved.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.0.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Group Leaders can now only view the Notes of Students in their own Groups, and additionally only those that the Students explicitly marked to be sent to an Instructor</li>\n<li>Group Leaders can view Notes from the backend properly now (Previously this was limited to only Administrators)</li>\n<li>Options have been included to automatically include the frontend workflows within all Courses if desired</li>\n</ul>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:114:\"The Notes add-on makes note-taking simple and opens up instructor communication during the student’s study time.\";s:7:\"banners\";a:2:{s:3:\"low\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"high\";s:0:\"\";}s:11:\"screenshots\";a:0:{}s:5:\"icons\";a:1:{s:7:\"default\";s:74:\"https://plugins.learndash.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/student-notes.svg\";}s:6:\"author\";s:9:\"LearnDash\";s:10:\"author_uri\";s:26:\"https://www.learndash.com/\";s:11:\"requires_ld\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"plugin_uri\";s:45:\"https://www.learndash.com/notes-by-learndash/\";s:4:\"tags\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"slug\";s:15:\"learndash-notes\";s:12:\"product_type\";s:7:\"premium\";s:12:\"is_purchased\";b:0;}s:19:\"learndash-gradebook\";a:20:{s:4:\"name\";s:9:\"Gradebook\";s:10:\"project_id\";i:170;s:14:\"latest_version\";s:5:\"4.3.2\";s:8:\"requires\";s:5:\"4.8.0\";s:6:\"tested\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"requires_php\";s:5:\"5.3.0\";s:12:\"last_updated\";s:19:\"2024-10-07 15:04:57\";s:8:\"sections\";a:3:{s:11:\"description\";s:209:\"Easily customize, track, and share scores with Gradebook. Explore student progression and scores in simple, flexible grade book tables, and share individual scores and progress with students and their parents.\";s:12:\"installation\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:2948:\"<strong>4.3.2</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Feature - The Overall Grade Block can now be used with LearnDash Certificates. Note: Requires Certificate Builder v1.1.2.</li>\n<li>Fix - Resolved LearnDash submenu items order issue.</li>\n<li>Fix - Resolved PHP deprecated notice started in PHP 8.2.</li>\n<li>Fix - Gradebook Letter and Color Scales are now more aggressively sanitized to ensure a fatal error cannot be hit if one were saved in an incorrect format.</li>\n<li>Fix - Fatal error on the gradebook view page when using the UTC timezone.</li>\n<li>Fix - Multiple typos and non-translatable strings.</li>\n<li>Fix - Resolved PHP deprecated notice started in PHP 8.2.</li>\n<li>Fix - Resolved saving styles settings always showing a &quot;Settings save failed&quot; notice even though they have successfully saved.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Updated functions: <code>ld_gb_get_timezone_offset</code>.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Added actions: <code>learndash_gradebook_uninstall</code>.</li>\n<li>Tweak: Added functions: <code>learndash_gradebook_sanitize_grade_style_settings</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>4.3.1.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix - Added additional validation for shortcodes.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>4.3.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix: Fixes an issue where certain fields were very large when editing different content types</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>4.3.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Feature: A new integration with LearnDash Notifications has been added. If both plugins are active, a new notification trigger for when a Manual Grade is added will show within the Notification creation form.\n\n<ul>\n<li>Note: This requires LearnDash Notifications v1.6.2 or higher to be installed.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>Feature: Ajax search for Gradebooks in the backend Gradebook</li>\n<li>Feature: Telemetry functionality added. This will be sent if telemetry is opted in for LearnDash itself.</li>\n<li>Fix: Ensures that an extra long Grade Name will wrap around properly.</li>\n<li>Fix: Addresses an edge case where a notice could show telling the user that there was an issue authenticating with the licensing server after it has successfully authenticated.</li>\n<li>Tweak: Quizzes with ungraded Essay Questions will now show as &quot;Pending&quot; within the Gradebook\n\n<ul>\n<li>The following templates have been updated for this change:</li>\n<li><code>./templates/frontend-gradebook/edit-panel/components/edit-panel-grade-row.php</code></li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>Tweak: Improved mobile display for both the backend and frontend Gradebooks</li>\n<li>Tweak: Adds additional styling in the event that there&#039;s an issue rendering a Gutenberg Block within the editor.</li>\n<li>Tweak: Improved returned error messages shown if there&#039;s an issue authenticating the plugin with the licensing server.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>4.2.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Prevents an issue where some users couldn&#039;t access the admin dashboard after upgrading to v4.2.0</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>4.2.0</strong><br/>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:209:\"Easily customize, track, and share scores with Gradebook. Explore student progression and scores in simple, flexible grade book tables, and share individual scores and progress with students and their parents.\";s:7:\"banners\";a:2:{s:3:\"low\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"high\";s:0:\"\";}s:11:\"screenshots\";a:0:{}s:5:\"icons\";a:1:{s:7:\"default\";s:72:\"https://plugins.learndash.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/gradebook-2.svg\";}s:6:\"author\";s:9:\"LearnDash\";s:10:\"author_uri\";s:26:\"https://www.learndash.com/\";s:11:\"requires_ld\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"plugin_uri\";s:49:\"https://www.learndash.com/gradebook-by-learndash/\";s:4:\"tags\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"slug\";s:19:\"learndash-gradebook\";s:12:\"product_type\";s:7:\"premium\";s:12:\"is_purchased\";b:0;}s:21:\"learndash-groups-plus\";a:20:{s:4:\"name\";s:11:\"Groups Plus\";s:10:\"project_id\";i:161;s:14:\"latest_version\";s:5:\"2.1.1\";s:8:\"requires\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"tested\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"requires_php\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"last_updated\";s:19:\"2024-04-23 15:20:38\";s:8:\"sections\";a:3:{s:11:\"description\";s:421:\"Extend the functionality of LearnDash Groups to allow your users to create and control their own organization. Users purchasing an organization can purchase a configurable number of seats to control the number of team members allowed within the organization.\r\n\r\nFront end management, reporting and grading means that your users can easily control the organization without needing access to the WP administrator dashboard.\";s:12:\"installation\";s:486:\"If the auto-update is not working, you always have the option to update manually. Please note, a full backup of your site is always recommended prior to updating.\r\n\r\nDeactivate and delete your current version of LearnDash Groups Plus.\r\nDownload the latest version of LearnDash Groups Plus from your account portal - https://account.learndash.com\r\nUpload the zipped file via PLUGINS &gt; ADD NEW, or to wp-content/plugins.\r\nActivate the LearnDash Groups Plus plugin via the PLUGINS menu.\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:4730:\"<strong>2.1.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix - Teams without any Courses assigned to them no longer show all Courses in the Course Filter dropdown in the Groups Plus frontend dashboard.</li>\n<li>Fix - Subscription Sign Up Fees are no longer added multiple times to a Subscription created to sell Groups Plus content.</li>\n<li>Fix - Seat Prices set for a specific Team are now applied correctly when purchasing a Seats Product.</li>\n<li>Fix - Variable Pre-Built Organization Products didn&#039;t grant the purchased Organization the Courses from the &quot;Source Organizations&quot; chosen for the purchased Variation.</li>\n<li>Fix - Subscriptions that had Expired or had been Cancelled would previously create a new Organization/Team or add the originally purchased number of Seats once again after the Subscription was resumed.</li>\n<li>Fix - Added additional validation for shortcodes.</li>\n<li>Fix - Fixed fatal error in the <code>total_time</code> shortcode.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>2.1.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix - Teams created via the Groups Plus Dashboard now inherit the set Access Mode from the Organization.</li>\n<li>Fix - Incompatibility with other plugins using psr/container.</li>\n<li>Fix - Fixes PHP 8.1+ warning for usage of deprecated <code>FILTER_SANITIZE_STRING</code>.</li>\n<li>Fix - Fixes an issue where a Variable Teams Product could not be created correctly.</li>\n<li>Fix - Fixes Organization and Team names showing with backslashes on the WooCommerce Cart screen in some scenarios.</li>\n<li>Fix - Variable Pre-Built Organization Products did not grant the correct number of Seats to the Organization itself after purchase.</li>\n<li>Fix - Incompatibility with the WooCommerce Cart Block.</li>\n<li>Fix - Incompatibility with the WooCommerce Checkout Block.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Adjusted layout of the Organization view of the frontend dashboard.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Changed Terminology for Pre-Built Organizations in the WooCommerce Product Tabs.</li>\n<li>Tweak - Added filters: <code>learndash_groups_plus_cart_item_data_name</code>, <code>learndash_groups_plus_cart_item_data_value</code>, <code>learndash_groups_plus_cart_item_data</code>, <code>learndash_groups_plus_organizations_valid_cart_item_data_keys</code>, <code>learndash_groups_plus_pre_built_organizations_valid_cart_item_data_keys</code>, <code>learndash_groups_plus_seats_valid_cart_item_data_keys</code>, <code>learndash_groups_plus_teams_valid_cart_item_data_keys</code></li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>2.0.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Feature: &quot;LearnDash Team&quot; Product Type added so that a Team can be sold outside of an Organization structure.\n\n<ul>\n<li>If not using the WooCommerce purchase workflow, a top-level Group can be recognized as a Team by checking the &quot;Disable Team creation?&quot; checkbox on the Group Edit screen in the Admin Dashboard.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>Fix: The &quot;Disable Change Password button&quot; and &quot;Disable Export CSV button&quot; settings now work as expected.</li>\n<li>Fix: A bug where a Team Leader could be unable to edit a Team Member when they should have been able to.</li>\n<li>Fix: A bug where if a Team under an Organization had 0 Seats remaining, it was impossible to purchase more Seats for that Team.</li>\n<li>Tweak: The following Product Types have been renamed to make their function clearer:\n\n<ul>\n<li>LearnDash Organization Product -&gt; LearnDash Organization</li>\n<li>LearnDash Organization Group Product -&gt; LearnDash Pre-Built Organization</li>\n<li>LearnDash Team Seat -&gt; LearnDash Seats</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.1.2</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix: Subscription renewal no longer creates copies of purchased Organizations.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.1.1</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Fix: untranslatable strings in admin and frontend pages.</li>\n<li>Fix: conflict with Pods plugin. User can&#039;t activate both plugin simultaneously.</li>\n<li>Security: improve security in user import feature.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.1.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Added - Migration for settings from legacy LearnDash Classrooms addon to new LearnDash Groups Plus addon.</li>\n<li>Added - Custom labels for LearnDash Groups Plus terms.</li>\n<li>Fix - Set email from header from lead organizer or team leader.</li>\n<li>Fix - Improve database table names to prevent conflicts.</li>\n<li>Fix - Some setting labels for clearer intent.</li>\n<li>Fix - Non group leader cannot change product quantity during purchase.</li>\n<li>Fix - User can purchase seat without setting the team first.</li>\n<li>Fix - &quot;Create a team&quot; form displays incorrect list of courses when there&#039;s no set courses in the parent organization group.</li>\n</ul>\n<br/><strong>1.0.0</strong><br/><ul>\n<li>Initial Release</li>\n</ul>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:118:\"The Groups Plus add-on empowers you to sell B2B learning solutions wi